# WHAT IT IS
#   Lightdash is the **open-source dbt-native BI platform** — the
#   metrics + dashboarding layer for analytics-engineering teams
#   that already invested in dbt.  Architectural positioning:
#
#     • **dbt-native** — every Lightdash metric / dimension /
#       explore is declared in the same `schema.yml` file as
#       the dbt model.  No separate semantic-layer YAML, no
#       LookML-style modeling tier.  The dbt project IS the
#       semantic layer.
#     • **Code-first + GitOps** — dashboards, charts, projects,
#       and metrics live in version-controlled YAML.  Preview
#       projects spawn ephemeral environments per PR (analogous
#       to Vercel/Netlify preview deployments, but for BI).
#     • **dbt-aware CLI** — `lightdash dbt run` proxies to
#       `dbt run` then regenerates the affected schema.yml
#       Lightdash blocks.  `lightdash compile` runs `dbt compile`
#       and validates the metrics graph.
#     • **Open-source vs hosted SaaS** — Apache-style core under
#       MIT; commercial features (SSO, audit logs, embedded
#       analytics, batched deploys, OPA RBAC) gated by
#       `enterprise/` workspace.
#     • **API + OIDC auth** — every API call is authenticated;
#       the CLI uses the OAuth 2.0 Authorization Code Flow with
#       PKCE (RFC 7636) via openid-client to obtain an access
#       token, opening the system browser to the Lightdash
#       server's `/oauth/authorize` endpoint.
#
#   The `lightdash` CLI is the analytics-engineer's daily driver:
#
#     • `lightdash login [url]`     OAuth 2.0 / OIDC PKCE login;
#                                    opens browser.  Alternatives:
#                                    `--token <PAT>` for service
#                                    accounts, `--email <addr>`
#                                    for local-dev password flow.
#     • `lightdash config set-project --name <name>` /
#       `lightdash config set-project --uuid <uuid>`
#                                    select active project
#                                    non-interactively
#     • `lightdash config list-projects` /
#       `lightdash config get-project` /
#       `lightdash config unset-project`
#                                    project-context inspection
#     • `lightdash dbt run -s mymodel` dbt-passthrough + schema.yml
#                                       regeneration
#     • `lightdash compile`         compile + validate Lightdash
#                                    metrics against dbt manifest
#     • `lightdash deploy`          compile then push explores
#                                    to active project
#     • `lightdash preview`         create ephemeral preview
#                                    project + wait for keypress
#     • `lightdash start-preview --name <name>`
#       `lightdash stop-preview --name <name>`
#                                    persistent preview lifecycle
#     • `lightdash download` / `lightdash upload`
#                                    pull/push dashboards + charts
#                                    as YAML artifacts (the
#                                    GitOps round-trip)
#     • `lightdash generate -s <model>`
#                                    auto-generate Lightdash blocks
#                                    in dbt schema.yml from
#                                    warehouse catalog
#     • `lightdash generate-exposures`
#                                    emit dbt exposures from
#                                    Lightdash charts (closes the
#                                    chart-to-model lineage loop)
#     • `lightdash refresh`         trigger a project refresh
#     • `lightdash validate`        run server-side validation on
#                                    the active project
#     • `lightdash lint -f file.yml`
#                                    static-validate Lightdash
#                                    block YAML
#     • `lightdash rename`          bulk rename metric/dimension/
#                                    explore identifiers
#     • `lightdash sql -q '<query>'`
#                                    execute SQL against the
#                                    Lightdash warehouse
#                                    connection
#     • `lightdash run-chart --uuid <chart-uuid>`
#                                    execute a saved chart
#                                    headlessly + return JSON
#     • `lightdash export-chart-image --uuid <chart-uuid>`
#                                    render chart to PNG/SVG
#     • `lightdash set-warehouse`   reconfigure project warehouse
#                                    credentials
#     • `lightdash diagnostics`     environment-introspection
#                                    bug-report bundle
#     • `lightdash pre-aggregate-audit`
#                                    detect dashboard queries
#                                    that would benefit from
#                                    materialized pre-aggregates
#     • `lightdash install-skills`  install the Lightdash AI
#                                    "skills" plugin set (the
#                                    LLM-tool-call surface that
#                                    lets Claude/GPT call the
#                                    Lightdash API)
#     • `lightdash help [command]`  per-command help
