# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `lightdash/lightdash`'s `packages/cli/package.json` declares a
#   **direct** dependency on `openid-client@5.6.4`.  The login
#   handler at `packages/cli/src/handlers/login.ts` constructs the
#   typed `Issuer.discover(serverUrl + '/oauth')` discovery client,
#   then the typed `client.authorizationUrl({ scope, code_challenge,
#   code_challenge_method: 'S256' })` PKCE URL, opens the browser,
#   captures the callback on a localhost port, calls typed
#   `client.callback(redirectUri, params, { code_verifier })` to
#   exchange the code for tokens, and persists the typed `Tokens`
#   in the `~/.config/lightdash/config.yaml` credential store.
#
#   `panva/node-openid-client` (`openid-client` on npm) is **THE
#   canonical Node.js OIDC library** — Filip Skokan's typed pure-
#   TypeScript implementation of the entire OAuth 2.0 + OpenID
#   Connect 1.0 protocol stack.  Filip Skokan is also the editor
#   of multiple OAuth/OIDC IETF + OpenID Foundation specifications
#   (RFC 9449 DPoP, RFC 9068 JWT Access Tokens, the OAuth 2.1
#   draft, the FAPI 2.0 Security Profile, JOSE WGs).  The library
#   has been in continuous active development since 2018, has
#   2,300+ ★ on github.com/panva/node-openid-client, and clocks
#   **9.5 million downloads per week** on npm (the dominant Node-
#   side OIDC dependency by 2 orders of magnitude vs alternatives
#   like `oidc-client-ts`, `passport-openidconnect`, or
#   `@auth0/auth0-js`).
#
#   openid-client v5 ships:
#
#     • Typed `Issuer.discover(url)`     OIDC Discovery 1.0
#                                        (`/.well-known/openid-
#                                        configuration`) endpoint
#                                        client with typed
#                                        `IssuerMetadata` —
#                                        every standard claim
#                                        (`issuer`,
#                                        `authorization_endpoint`,
#                                        `token_endpoint`,
#                                        `userinfo_endpoint`,
#                                        `jwks_uri`,
#                                        `registration_endpoint`,
#                                        `scopes_supported`,
#                                        `response_types_supported`,
#                                        `response_modes_supported`,
#                                        `grant_types_supported`,
#                                        `acr_values_supported`,
#                                        `subject_types_supported`,
#                                        `id_token_signing_alg_values_supported`,
#                                        `userinfo_signing_alg_values_supported`,
#                                        `request_object_signing_alg_values_supported`,
#                                        `token_endpoint_auth_methods_supported`,
#                                        `token_endpoint_auth_signing_alg_values_supported`,
#                                        `claims_supported`,
#                                        `code_challenge_methods_supported`,
#                                        `revocation_endpoint`,
#                                        `introspection_endpoint`,
#                                        `device_authorization_endpoint`,
#                                        `pushed_authorization_request_endpoint`,
#                                        `end_session_endpoint`,
#                                        `frontchannel_logout_supported`,
#                                        `backchannel_logout_supported`,
#                                        `backchannel_authentication_endpoint`,
#                                        `backchannel_token_delivery_modes_supported`,
#                                        `backchannel_user_code_parameter_supported`)
#                                        typed accessors
#     • Typed `Client.authorizationUrl()`
#                                        OAuth 2.0 Authorization
#                                        Code Flow URL builder
#                                        with typed PKCE
#                                        (`code_challenge`,
#                                        `code_challenge_method`),
#                                        typed `state`, typed
#                                        `nonce`, typed
#                                        `response_mode`, typed
#                                        `acr_values`, typed
#                                        `prompt`, typed
#                                        `max_age`, typed
#                                        `id_token_hint`, typed
#                                        `login_hint`, typed
#                                        `claims`, typed
#                                        `claims_locales`, typed
#                                        `ui_locales`, typed
#                                        request-object signing
#                                        (`request`,
#                                        `request_uri`)
#     • Typed `Client.callback()`        OAuth 2.0 Authorization
#                                        Code Exchange with typed
#                                        PKCE verification, typed
#                                        `iss` validation (RFC
#                                        9207), typed `state`
#                                        validation, typed `c_hash`
#                                        + `at_hash` + `s_hash`
#                                        validation, typed JWT
#                                        validation chain
#     • Typed `Client.refresh()`         OAuth 2.0 Refresh Token
#                                        Grant
#     • Typed `Client.userinfo()`        OIDC UserInfo endpoint
#                                        with typed `UserInfo`
#                                        claim envelope
#     • Typed `Client.introspect()`      RFC 7662 Token
#                                        Introspection
#     • Typed `Client.revoke()`          RFC 7009 Token Revocation
#     • Typed `Client.deviceAuthorization()`
#                                        RFC 8628 OAuth 2.0 Device
#                                        Authorization Grant (the
#                                        canonical "device flow"
#                                        for TVs/CLIs/IoT — used
#                                        by `gh auth login`, `aws
#                                        sso login`, `terraform
#                                        login`)
#     • Typed `Client.requestObject()`   RFC 9101 JAR (JWT-Secured
#                                        Authorization Request) +
#                                        RFC 9126 PAR (Pushed
#                                        Authorization Requests)
#     • Typed `Client.endSessionUrl()`   OIDC RP-Initiated Logout
#                                        1.0
#     • Typed `Client.dpopProof()`       RFC 9449 OAuth 2.0
#                                        Demonstrating Proof of
#                                        Possession (DPoP) JWT
#                                        signer
#     • Typed `generators.codeVerifier()`
#       Typed `generators.codeChallenge()`
#       Typed `generators.nonce()`
#       Typed `generators.state()`       RFC 7636 PKCE +
#                                        cryptographically-random
#                                        nonce/state generators
#     • Typed `Strategy` for passport.js (the canonical
#                                        passport-openidconnect
#                                        replacement)
#     • Typed FAPI 1.0 + FAPI 2.0 Security Profile compliance
#                                        modes
#     • Typed mTLS-bound access tokens   (RFC 8705 OAuth 2.0
#                                        Mutual-TLS Client
#                                        Authentication +
#                                        Certificate-Bound Access
#                                        Tokens)
#     • Typed JWT validation             with full JWS / JWE
#                                        algorithm coverage:
#                                        RS256, RS384, RS512,
#                                        PS256, PS384, PS512,
#                                        ES256, ES384, ES512,
#                                        EdDSA, HS256, HS384,
#                                        HS512
#     • Typed JWKS rotation              via the integrated
#                                        `jose` library with
#                                        typed in-memory cache
#     • Typed dynamic client registration
#                                        (RFC 7591 + RFC 7592)
#
#   `openid-client` is the OIDC library behind essentially every
#   modern Node.js OIDC integration in production:
#
#     • **Auth.js / NextAuth.js** — the dominant Next.js
#       authentication library (24,000+ ★) wraps openid-client
#       for every OIDC provider entry (Google / Microsoft / Auth0
#       / Okta / Keycloak / Authentik / Cognito / Twitch /
#       Discord OIDC profiles)
#     • **n8n** — the open-source workflow automation tool
#       (50,000+ ★)
#     • **Immich** — the self-hosted Google Photos alternative
#       (45,000+ ★;  covered as `_immich` elsewhere in corpus)
#     • **HedgeDoc** — the collaborative markdown editor
#     • **OpenAPI Tools / lightdash** (this very project)
#     • **Strapi** — the headless CMS (60,000+ ★) plugin set
#     • **Cal.com** — the open-source Calendly alternative
#     • **Plane** — the open-source Jira alternative
#     • **Mattermost Boards** — the project board plugin
#     • **Twenty CRM** — the open-source Salesforce alternative
#     • **Infisical** — the open-source HashiCorp Vault
#       alternative
#     • **MCP Hub** — the Model Context Protocol broker
#     • **Lightdash CLI** — this binary
#     • **ToolJet** — the low-code internal-tools builder
#     • **Actual Budget** — the self-hosted YNAB alternative
#     • **GROWI** — the wiki / collaboration platform
#     • **Nexterm** — the self-hosted SSH/RDP gateway
#     • Plus thousands of internal SSO gateways, identity
#       brokers, and OIDC-protected Node microservices.
#
#   OAuth 2.0 + OpenID Connect (OIDC) collectively form **the
#   universal identity + authorization protocol of the modern
#   web** — standardized by the IETF (OAuth 2.0: RFC 6749 base +
#   RFC 6750 Bearer + RFC 7009 Revocation + RFC 7591 Dynamic
#   Client Registration + RFC 7592 + RFC 7636 PKCE + RFC 7662
#   Token Introspection + RFC 8252 OAuth 2.0 for Native Apps +
#   RFC 8628 Device Grant + RFC 8705 mTLS + RFC 9068 JWT Bearer +
